    "minides": "Lotus's last ICE-powered sports car — a lightweight, mid-engine coupe offered with a choice of an AMG-sourced turbo-four or a Toyota-derived supercharged V6, with a manual gearbox available only on the V6.",
    "description": "The Lotus Emira is Lotus's final internal-combustion sports car before the brand transitions to full electrification, launched in India in January 2025 at Rs 3.22 crore (ex-showroom). It is a lightweight, mid-engine, rear-wheel-drive coupe offered in two distinct powertrains: a 2.0-litre AMG-sourced turbocharged inline-4 producing around 360 hp paired exclusively with an 8-speed dual-clutch transmission, and a Toyota-sourced supercharged 3.5-litre V6 producing around 400+ hp, available with either a 6-speed manual or an automatic gearbox. The range spans Turbo, Turbo SE, and V6 SE trims. Despite its raw, driver-focused mission, the Emira features a notably modern cabin with a 12.3-inch touchscreen, 10.25-inch digital driver display, KEF premium audio, and even a partial ADAS suite including adaptive cruise control and collision mitigation. It directly rivals the Porsche 911 Carrera in India, particularly since the Porsche 718 Cayman has been discontinued."
  },
